# ECB Architecture

## Layer Responsibilities

- `boundary`: handles external I/O (UI, API, CLI), request validation, and response formatting.
- `control`: coordinates use cases, orchestrates entity operations, and enforces application-level policy.
- `entity`: defines domain models and invariants, encapsulates core business rules, independent from I/O/frameworks.

## Dependency Direction

- Allowed: `boundary -> control`, `control -> entity`
- Forbidden: `control -> boundary`, `entity -> control`, `entity -> boundary`, `boundary -> entity`

## Design Constraints

- Keep implementation details aligned to the target layer.
- Do not leak transport, framework, or persistence concerns into `entity`.
- Preserve clean layer contracts when adding or refactoring behavior.
